{
  "family": "Hofmann-L\u00f6ffler-Freytag Reaction (Remote Functionalization)",
  "candidate": {
    "substrate_smiles": [
      "CCCCN(C)Cl"
    ],
    "product_smiles": [
      "C1CCCN1C"
    ],
    "optional_reagent_smiles": [
      "O.O=S(=O)(O)O"
    ],
    "rationale": "This is a classic and simple example of the Hofmann-L\u00f6ffler-Freytag reaction. The substrate, N-chloro-N-methylbutan-1-amine, undergoes a 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer upon treatment with acid (e.g., sulfuric acid) and light/heat, followed by cyclization to form the pyrrolidine ring. The reaction demonstrates the key features: formation of a nitrogen-centered radical, intramolecular hydrogen abstraction from a delta-carbon, and subsequent cyclization to form a five-membered ring. The use of a simple N-methylbutylamine derivative keeps the structure acyclic and minimal.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The core transformation is an intramolecular C-H amination via a radical mechanism, specifically forming a pyrrolidine from an N-haloamine. This specific substrate (N-chloro-N-methylbutan-1-amine) and product (N-methylpyrrolidine) are highly characteristic of this named reaction and avoid motifs common to other families like arenes (Hofmann-Martius), amides (Hofmann rearrangement), or alkenes (Hofmann elimination)."
  }
}
